 gender. Discounted Labour is an essential new work for anyone interested in the historical struggle for gender equality in Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSexual division of laborzCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aSexual division of laborzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxEmploymentzCanadaxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomenxEmploymentzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aPatrias, Carmela, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262749940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442627499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442627499/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK